# Protein Tracker Project Structure

This is a full-stack protein tracking application with a Flutter frontend and Node.js backend.

## Project Architecture
- **Frontend**: Flutter app located in [frontend/](mdc:frontend/) directory
- **Backend**: Node.js/Express API located in [backend/](mdc:backend/) directory

## Key Frontend Files
- [main.dart](mdc:frontend/lib/main.dart) - Main Flutter application entry point
- [pubspec.yaml](mdc:frontend/pubspec.yaml) - Flutter dependencies and configuration
- [analysis_options.yaml](mdc:frontend/analysis_options.yaml) - Dart/Flutter linting rules

## Key Backend Files
- [index.js](mdc:backend/index.js) - Express server entry point
- [package.json](mdc:backend/package.json) - Node.js dependencies and scripts
- [env.example](mdc:backend/env.example) - Environment variables template

## Development Workflow
- Frontend: Use `flutter run` in the frontend directory
- Backend: Use `npm start` or `node index.js` in the backend directory
- Both should run simultaneously for full-stack development
